OL,3,CIt's another hold but Bank of England
OL,4,Csignals August cut is on the cards
OL,6,FThe minutes repeat the concern about
OL,7,Fthe "tightness" of the labour market
OL,8,Fbut also note that unemployment is
OL,9,Frising and the number of vacancies in
OL,10,Fthe economy continues to fall.
OL,12,FThe minutes also state that some of
OL,13,Fthose who voted to hold - a group
OL,14,Fwhich included the governor Andrew
OL,15,FBailey - feel the economy is still on
OL,16,Fa "disinflationary trajectory".
